sentences: Margaret Pardee Butterly (May 10, 1920 – January 26, 2016) was an American violinist and violin teacher.
In her mid-eighties, she donated a set of 30 violins and violas to the Juilliard School, including a 1771 Guadagnini violin, an 1845 Gagliano violin, and an 1810 J.B. Ceruti half-size violin.
She taught at Juilliard for over 60 years.
She also taught at the Meadowmount School of Music summer programs.
In addition to mentoring her students, she was a surrogate mother to many and housed one or two students at a time for many years.
In an interview she reveled in the success of her students and the fact that she continued to hear from them in later years.
